{{Infobox journal | title = African and Black Diaspora | cover = 2016 cover African and Black Diaspora.jpg | abbreviation = Afr. Black Diaspora | discipline = [[African studies]], [[Black studies]], [[African diaspora]] | publisher = [[Routledge]] | country = | history = 2008–present | frequency = Biannually | website = http://www.tandfonline.com/action/journalInformation?journalCode=rabd20 | link1 = http://www.tandfonline.com/toc/rabd20/current | link1-name = Online access | link2 = http://www.tandfonline.com/loi/rabd20 | link2-name = Online archive | ISSN = 1752-8631 | eISSN = 1752-864X | JSTOR = | OCLC = 154200895 | LCCN = 2007213166 }} '''''African and Black Diaspora: An International Journal''''' is a biannual [[peer-reviewed]] [[academic journal]] covering [[African studies|African]] and [[Black studies]], as well as research on the [[African diaspora]]. It was established in 2008 and is published by [[Routledge]]. The [[editors-in-chief]] are Fassil Demissie ([[DePaul University]]) and Sandra Jackson (DePaul University).<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.tandfonline.com/action/journalInformation?show=editorialBoard&journalCode=rabd20 |title=Editorial Board |work=African and Black Diaspora |publisher=[[Routledge]] |accessdate=2016-11-27}}</ref>
