{{Infobox book | name = A Ramachandran: A Retrospective | title_orig = | translator = | image = Ramachandran - A Retrospective.jpg | caption = | author = [[R. Siva Kumar]] | illustrator = | cover_artist = | country = India | language = English | series = | subject = A Ramachandran's Paintings and Philosophy of Art | genre = Art | publisher = Vadehra Art Gallery | pub_date = 2004 | english_pub_date = | pages = 548 | isbn = 9788187737049 | oclc = | preceded_by = | followed_by = }} '''''A Ramachandran: A Retrospective''''' (2004), is a two-volume book by Indian art historian [[R. Siva Kumar]].<ref name="google">{{cite book|title=Ramachandran, a Retrospective|author1=Ramachandran, A.|author2=Kumar, R.S.|author3=National Gallery of Modern Art (New Delhi, India)|date=2004|volume=1|publisher=Vadehra Art Gallery|isbn=9788187737049|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=8P3pAAAAMAAJ|accessdate=2015-02-11}}</ref> It is a study of the life and works of artist [[A. Ramachandran]]. It has more than 500 reproductions and a selection of rare, historical photographs. Selected writings by the artist, biographical notes and chronology of works are also included in the book.
According to the publisher, the book "may well be considered a model in writing about an artist and his work, and will be of immense value to coming generations of art scholars and connoisseurs."<ref name="swb">{{cite web|url=http://www.swb.co.in/store/book/ramachandran-retrospective|title=Ramachandran, A Retrospective&#124; Book&#124; Store &#124;SWB &#124; Scholars without Borders, an online academic bookstore in India|publisher=swb.co.in|accessdate=2015-02-11}}</ref> It is the most comprehensive book on [[A. Ramachandran]]'s art.{{citation needed|date=September 2013}}
